g.text: Feature Impact on Systolic Blood Pressure Prediction
• Limited Predictive Power: Systolic BP shows R² = 0.006, indicating climate has minimal direct impact
• Wind Speed Dominance: Most important climate feature (4.7% importance) suggests air movement effects
• Sex as Confounder: Second most important feature (4.6%) confirms demographic control necessity
• Temperature Range Effects: Daily temperature variation more predictive than absolute values
• Non-linear Relationships: SHAP dependency plots reveal complex climate-health interactions
• Better Results for Metabolic Markers: Glucose (R²=0.29) and CD4 (R²=0.22) show stronger climate associations
• Temporal Lags Matter: Multiple lag features (0, 1, 7 days) capture delayed climate effects
• Heat Index Importance: Combined temperature-humidity measures outperform individual variables
